        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 3 at 2:03PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 202 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
McLeansville, or 10 miles south of Reidsville, moving north at 35
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts in excess of 30 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Greensboro, McLeansville, Haw River State Park, Lake Townsend Marina,
Lake Townsend, and Monticello.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
